President Donald J. Trump spoke with Acting President Hwang Kyo-Ahn of South Korea about the recent chemical weapons attack in Syria. They agreed that the use of such weapons cannot be tolerated and that the international community should work together to prevent further use. President Trump thanked Acting President Hwang for his support for the US strikes in Syria. They also discussed the strong alliance between the US and South Korea and agreed to stay in close contact regarding North Korea and other mutual concerns.